This paper discusses the issue of bias in online information, which is a topic that is relevant to several sub-categories in computer science. However, the most likely sub-category is Information Retrieval (cs.IR) since the paper focuses on search engines and recommendation services. Other relevant sub-categories include Social and Information Networks (cs.SI), Computers and Society (cs.CY), Social Computing (cs.SOC), and Computation and Language (cs.CL) since the paper also discusses the role of social networks and language in bias.
